						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is having to relocate to an area with <span class="posthilit">a</span> high cost of <span class="posthilit">living</span> one of the things keeping people out of professional video game development?</div><br /><br />I don't think that's <span class="posthilit">a</span> huge factor. The cost of <span class="posthilit">living</span> in California is fairly high (esp. San Francisco), but the lower paid jobs in the industry tend to be filled by locals who are already used to paying that high cost, and <span class="posthilit">for</span> the higher paid jobs I don't think it's as big an issue. There are also (fewer) companies in places where the cost of <span class="posthilit">living</span> is fairly low, like CD Projekt in Poland.</div>

